Description: TUI University - Online School is a school.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Trident University International (TUI) is a fully online school where students can obtain a certification, bachelor’s degree, master’s degree, or PhD in an array of professional fields. The following types of study areas are offered at TUI:   * Business Administration   * Computer Science   * Conflict Resolution Management   * Educational Leadership   * Emergency and Disaster Management   * Information Technology In order for students to obtain a bachelor’s degree, they need to commit to schooling for four years. Master’s degrees take about two and a half years, and doctorate degrees can take up to six years. The majority of the students at TUI are military personnel who are looking for workforce education and training. There are also non-military students who attend the university. Undergraduate and graduate admissions requirements include submitting enrollment applications, official transcripts, and proof of earning a high school diploma or an undergraduate degree. For doctoral programs, applicants must have a minimum 3.4 GPA. There is no application fee to apply for bachelor’s and master’s degree programs, however there is an application fee to apply for doctoral programs. There are different admissions criteria for military applicants. Regarding financial aid, military education benefits are accepted at TUI. There may be other financial aid resources available for eligible applicants as well through federal government programs and other private sources.

Soin International, LLC, through its subsidiaries, is engaged in equity investment, information technology (IT) and BPO services, large
Full Description: Soin International, LLC, through its subsidiaries, is engaged in equity investment, information technology (IT) and BPO services, large aluminum and steel parts and electromechanical assemblies fabrication and manufacturing, and residential land development businesses. It focuses on recapitalization and buy-outs targeting well-run and small-to mid-size companies. The company is also engaged in providing system design and integration, internal business applications, procurement, IT outsourcing, and supply chain services; and manufacturing custom compression molded thermoplastic and thermoset composite materials for consumer and industrial applications. Its consumer plastic products include snow sleds, wakeboards, plastic composite basketball backboards and bases, plastic wagons for children, and lawn and garden carts; and plastic products for the industrial sector include plastic dumpster lids, molded pallets, and various automotive related accessory items. In addition, it is specialized in the fabrication and manufacture of parts, such as turret rings and weapon mounts used on vehicles, various parts, and assemblies for up-armored military vehicles, escalators, conveyors, mining chains, valve bodies, printing presses, lift trucks, prison window sills, and various types of military tank target lifters used to lift a tank silhouette for live fire training. The company provides its aluminum and steel parts and electromechanical assemblies for the department of defense or commercial customers. Further, it is engaged in the acquisition of undeveloped land and its conversion into improved residential building sites. The company serves customers in the United States and internationally. Soin International, LLC was formerly known as MTC International, LLC and changed the name to Soin International, LLC in April 2002. The company was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Dayton, Ohio with additional offices in North America, Europe, and India.
